<li>Moreover , the cysteine residues of NlpE are critical for activating the CpxR / CpxA system in E. coli [ 34 ] , and a periplasmic LolA de-rivative with an artificial disulfide bond activates the CpxR/CpxA system [ 35 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23031642" target="_blank">23031642</a>]<br></li>
<li>It also suggests that other members of the CpxR regulon are not essential for SPI1 TTSS function .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14679226" target="_blank">14679226</a>]<br></li>
